1. To intialize the git in the project repo : git init

2. To check the status : git status

3. To link the global repo with the local : git config --global user.name "username"
			                  : git config --global user.email "github account email"

4. To add something in gits attention : git add

5. To commit changes : git commit -m "message here"

6. To push your local file globally : git push

7. To add brach : git branch "brachname"

8. To navigate through the repo : git checkout masters
				: git checkout "brach name"

9. To download the repo : git pull

10. To mirror your local repo with git account : git remote add origin http://github.com/username/foldertitleofgit.git

11. To confirm the above statement mirroring : git remote -v

12. More specific push : git push origin master

13. Remove existing remote repo : git remote rm origin /* origin is the name of the repo */

13. CHange the remote origin : git remote set-url origin http://github.com/username/foldertitleofgit.git
